title: SpaceX Acquires Dragon Parachute Maker Pioneer Aerospace In $2.2 Million Bankruptcy Deal
summary: SpaceX has acquired Pioneer Aerospace, a renowned leader in spacecraft parachute manufacturing.

title: Astra Secures $2.7M In Funding As Future Still Unclear
summary: Astra Space has successfully raised $2.7 million from existing investors, according to a filing submitted to the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.

title: Launch Roundup: Soyuz to resupply the ISS; SpaceX to launch more Starlink satellites
summary: This week, SpaceX looks to continue its incredible launch cadence with two more launches of Falcon 9 and a Soyuz 2.1a plans to resupply the International Space Station (ISS).

title: Arctic broadband satellites complete key tests ahead of mid-2024 launch
summary: Two satellites designed to bring mobile broadband coverage to the Arctic region for civilians and military users have completed key tests ahead of their planned launch next summer.

title: Satellite imagery reveals explosion at China’s Jiuquan spaceport
summary: A Chinese launch vehicle maker appears to have suffered an explosion at a test site at Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center.
